On Wednesday, April 16, 2003, at 04:24PM, Mike Ross <mjross81(-at-)swbell.net> wrote:

>Could this possibly be caused by a vacuum leak?  Any help is appreciated.

It could be. Hook up a vacuum gauge and find out. It's a great diagnostic tool than only costs $20 at the flaps.

It could also be a fuel delivery problem (clogged filter, weak fuel pump, boogie man in your pressure regulator). 

